192013-05-08
ORDER: On May 3, 2013, Defendant filed a motion to dismiss. Pursuant to Rule 3.F. of this Court's Individual Practices in Civil Cases, on or before May 13, 2013, Plaintiff must notify the Court and its adversary in writing whether it intends to file an amended pleading and when it will do so or whether it will instead rely on the pleading being attacked. If Plaintiff elects not to amend its complaint, no further opportunities to amend will be granted and the motion to dismiss will proceed in the regular course. If Plaintiff chooses to amend, Defendant may then (a) file an answer; (b) file a new motion to dismiss; or (c) submit a letter stating that it relies on the initially-filed motion to dismiss. Nothing in this Order alters the time to amend, answer or move provided by the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure or Local Rules. The initial pretrial conference scheduled for May 31, 2013 is adjourned pending resolution of this motion. (Signed by Judge Alison J. Nathan on 5/8/2013) (cd) (Entered: 05/09/2013)
